---
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import "../../styles.css";
import {getLangFromUrl} from "../../i18n/utils";
const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
---

<html lang={lang}>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
    <title>Thesis</title>
</head>

<Header/>
<body class="text-amber-50 bg-gray-900">


<div style="height: calc(100dvh - 64px - 68px)">
    <!-- 64px is the height of the header, 68px is the height of the footer. TODO prerobit!! -->
    <div class="items-center mx-44">
        <h1 class="text-center font-bold  font-sans text-8xl pt-32">Association rule methods and their applications</h1>
        <p class="text-3xl mt-32 font-mono"><span class="font-semibold">Author:</span> Vasyl Khorev</p>
        <p class="text-3xl mt-2 font-mono"><span class="font-semibold">Thesis supervisor:</span> doc. RNDr. Ľubomír Antoni,
            PhD.</p>
        <p class="text-3xl mt-2 font-mono"><span class="font-semibold">Consultant:</span> prof. RNDr. Stanislav Krajči,
            PhD.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="mx-44 flex justify-start mt-20 gap-10">
        <a href="https://s.ics.upjs.sk/~vasyl_khorev/prezentacia.pdf">
            <button type="button"
                    class="font-mono  block rounded-md bg-gray-800 px-3 py-2 text-base font-medium text-white hover:bg-gray-700">
                <p>Presentation</p></button>
        </a>
        <a href="https://s.ics.upjs.sk/~vasyl_khorev/esej.pdf">
            <button type="button"
                    class="font-mono  block rounded-md bg-gray-800 px-3 py-2 text-base font-medium text-white hover:bg-gray-700">
                <p>Essay</p></button>
        </a>
        <a href="https://s.ics.upjs.sk/~vasyl_khorev/bakalarska_praca.pdf">
            <button type="button"
                    class="font-mono block rounded-md bg-gray-800 px-3 py-2 text-base font-medium text-white hover:bg-gray-700">
                <p>Thesis</p></button>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="flex items-center justify-center">
    <div class="flex flex-col w-3/4">
        <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-center underline underline-offset-8">Goals</div>
        <div class="text-2xl my-10">
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc">
                <li>Describe known algorithms for generating association rules.</li>
                <li>Implement known algorithms for generating association rules and compare their advantages and
                    disadvantages.
                </li>
                <li>Apply the implemented algorithms to a selected dataset.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 text-3xl font-bold text-center underline underline-offset-8"><a
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Association_rule_learning">What
            are Association Rules?</a></div>
        <div class="flex justify-center flex-col text-2xl my-10">
            Association occurs when several events are interrelated. It indicates that certain data (or events found in the data) are associated with other data or events resulting from the data.
            For example, a study conducted in a supermarket may show that 65% of visitors who buy potato chips will also buy Coca-Cola, and if there is a discount for such a set they will buy it 85% of the time.
            <img class="justify-self-center self-center  m-5 w-1/3 invert" src="/src/content/en/a_rule.png">
            If the store has information about such an association, it is easy for managers to judge how effective the discount is.
            These associations are called rules. Those that exceed a certain threshold are considered interesting. Such rules help in decision making and explanation.
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


</body>
<Footer/>

</html>